<subSubSection id="569A652CFFF49E057FCFFEAA0DF63F5A" pageId="14" pageNumber="518" type="key">
<key id="6A116196FFF49E057FCFFEAA0DF63F5A" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<keyStep id="A5742E02FFF49E057FCFFEAA0DF63B28" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<paragraph id="1E3F36A7FFF49E057FCFFEAA0DF63B0F" blockId="14.[151,1436,328,379]" box="[151,1436,328,350]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<keyLead id="A5719592FFF49E057FCFFEAA0DF63B0F" box="[151,1436,328,350]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis id="2CF4EAB5FFF49E057FCFFEAA08C93B0F" bold="true" box="[151,163,328,349]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">1</emphasis>
Labium with one pair of premental setae................................................................... 
<emphasis id="2CF4EAB5FFF49E057AC8FEAA0DF63B0F" bold="true" box="[1424,1436,328,349]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">2</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1E3F36A7FFF49E057FCFFE870DF63B28" blockId="14.[151,1436,328,379]" box="[151,1436,357,379]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<keyLead id="A5719592FFF49E057FCFFE870DF63B28" box="[151,1436,357,379]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis id="2CF4EAB5FFF49E057FCFFE8708C63B29" bold="true" box="[151,172,357,379]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">1’</emphasis>
Labium with more than one pair of premental setae.......................................................... 
<emphasis id="2CF4EAB5FFF49E057AC8FE870DF63B28" bold="true" box="[1424,1436,357,378]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">6</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="A5742E02FFF49E057FCFFE420DF63B81" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<paragraph id="1E3F36A7FFF49E057FCFFE420DF63BE7" blockId="14.[151,1436,416,468]" box="[151,1436,416,438]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<keyLead id="A5719592FFF49E057FCFFE420DF63BE7" box="[151,1436,416,438]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis id="2CF4EAB5FFF49E057FCFFE4208C93BE7" bold="true" box="[151,163,416,437]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">2</emphasis>
Palpal setae with same length; vertical lamella caudal gills.................................................... 
<emphasis id="2CF4EAB5FFF49E057AC8FE420DF63BE7" bold="true" box="[1424,1436,416,437]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">3</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1E3F36A7FFF49E057FCFFE5F0DF63B81" blockId="14.[151,1436,416,468]" box="[151,1436,445,468]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<keyLead id="A5719592FFF49E057FCFFE5F0DF63B81" box="[151,1436,445,468]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis id="2CF4EAB5FFF49E057FCFFE5F08C13B81" bold="true" box="[151,171,445,467]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">2’</emphasis>
Palpal setae with different length; triquetro - quadrate caudal gills (
<figureCitation id="86BB2A22FFF49E057C3EFE5F0BD43B86" box="[870,958,445,468]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="12.[151,250,1632,1656]" captionTargetBox="[151,1425,189,1607]" captionTargetId="figure-17@12.[151,1436,181,1608]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURE 13. Drawing of median gill of larva of representatives of Asian Platycnemididae: (A), Calicnemia gulinensis,redrawn from Chen &amp; Yu (2020); (B), Disparoneura apicalis, dorsal view, redrawn from Fraser (1943); (C), Nososticta moluccensis, redrawn from Lieftinck (1953); (D), Coeliccia flavostriata, redrawn from Orr &amp; Dow (2016); (E), Coeliccia campioni, redrawn from Orr &amp; Dow (2016); (F), Caconeura gomphoides, redrawn from Fraser (1943); (G), Onychargia atrocyana, redrawn from Orr &amp; Dow (2015b); (H), Indocnemis orang, this study; (I), Copera chantaburii, redrawn from Saetung et al. (2020); (J), Coeliccia cyanomelas, redrawn from Xu (2013); (K), Prodasineura autumnalis, redrawn from Lieftinck (1953); (L), Platycnemis echigoana redrawn from Ishida (1996); (M), Pseudocopera ciliata redrawn from Saetung et al. (2020). Arrows indicate nodus of caudal gills." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6541726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6541726/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">Fig. 13A</figureCitation>
), triradiate in transverse section.... 
<taxonomicName id="D9804D24FFF49E057A73FE5F0DF63B81" authorityName="Strand" authorityYear="1928" box="[1323,1436,445,467]" class="Insecta" family="Platycnemididae" genus="Calicnemia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="14" pageNumber="518" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2CF4EAB5FFF49E057A73FE5F0DF63B81" bold="true" box="[1323,1436,445,467]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">Calicnemia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="A5742E02FFF49E057FCFFE1A0DF63879" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<paragraph id="1E3F36A7FFF49E057FCFFE1A0DF6385F" blockId="14.[151,1436,504,556]" box="[151,1436,504,526]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<keyLead id="A5719592FFF49E057FCFFE1A0DF6385F" box="[151,1436,504,526]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis id="2CF4EAB5FFF49E057FCFFE1A08C9385F" bold="true" box="[151,163,504,525]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">3</emphasis>
2–4 palpal setae; weakly and moderately produced ligula; caudal gills with or without petiole......................... 
<emphasis id="2CF4EAB5FFF49E057AC8FE1A0DF6385F" bold="true" box="[1424,1436,504,525]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">4</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1E3F36A7FFF49E057FCFFDF70DF63879" blockId="14.[151,1436,504,556]" box="[151,1436,533,556]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<keyLead id="A5719592FFF49E057FCFFDF70DF63879" box="[151,1436,533,556]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis id="2CF4EAB5FFF49E057FCFFDF708C13879" bold="true" box="[151,171,533,555]" pageId="14" pageNumber="518">3’</emphasis>
6 palpal setae; strongly produced ligula; foliate caudal gills with distinct petiole (
